WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.041 --> 00:00:10.840
<i>Previously on</i> The Affair...

2
00:00:10.911 --> 00:00:12.209
Welcome to the end of the world.

3
00:00:12.279 --> 00:00:14.157
<i>Do you remember the
first time you saw her?</i>

4
00:00:14.181 --> 00:00:15.581
<i>Like it was yesterday.</i>

5
00:00:15.682 --> 00:00:17.048
I'm Noah. by the way.

6
00:00:17.117 --> 00:00:19.416
- What are we talking about?
- Noah's new book.

7
00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:21.664
Great. I didn't know there
was enough to talk about yet.

8
00:00:21.688 --> 00:00:24.089
<i>Uh. well. I haven't really
gotten too far with it.</i>

9
00:00:24.191 --> 00:00:25.401
<i>Is she flirting with you?</i>

10
00:00:25.425 --> 00:00:27.690
- Do you want to get out of here?
<i>- ♪ Dramatic music ♪</i>

11
00:00:27.761 --> 00:00:29.457
I don't want to divorce
you. you asshole!

12
00:00:29.563 --> 00:00:31.464
What... what do you want?

13
00:00:31.565 --> 00:00:34.000
I want you to come home.

14
00:00:34.101 --> 00:00:36.935
It's extraordinary. I want
it in stores by next fall.

15
00:00:37.004 --> 00:00:38.905
<i>I don't want this life.</i>

16
00:00:38.972 --> 00:00:42.101
<i>I have to leave. I'm in
love with someone else.</i>

17
00:00:42.175 --> 00:00:45.976
You have chosen to divorce in
what I like to call a humane way.

18
00:00:46.079 --> 00:00:48.344
<i>I blew up my life
for you. Alison.</i>

19
00:00:48.448 --> 00:00:50.393
I don't belong to you.
We're not living in your book.

20
00:00:50.417 --> 00:00:51.646
You can't control me.

21
00:00:55.956 --> 00:00:57.618
I'm pregnant.

22
00:00:59.326 --> 00:01:01.158
I don't know who
Joanie's father is.

23
00:01:01.228 --> 00:01:02.958
I never want to see you again.

24
00:01:03.030 --> 00:01:04.828
And I thought she
had done it deliberately

25
00:01:04.898 --> 00:01:08.266
<i>to trap me. make sure I
could never go back to you.</i>

26
00:01:14.441 --> 00:01:15.500
Fuck!

27
00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:19.839
It was a deer. It was a deer!

28
00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:26.584
Alison. if I don't do something.
they're gonna convict me.

29
00:01:26.653 --> 00:01:28.713
<i>I know. just...
Just tell the truth.</i>

30
00:01:28.789 --> 00:01:32.282
Your Honor. I'm guilty.
I killed Scott Lockhart.

31
00:01:32.392 --> 00:01:34.623
What the hell are
you doing? Sit down.

32
00:01:46.440 --> 00:01:49.035
<i>♪ I was screaming
into the canyon ♪</i>

33
00:01:49.142 --> 00:01:52.476
<i>♪ At the moment of my death ♪</i>

34
00:01:52.546 --> 00:01:55.983
<i>♪ The echo I created ♪</i>

35
00:01:56.049 --> 00:01:59.144
<i>♪ Outlasted my last breath ♪</i>

36
00:01:59.219 --> 00:02:02.383
<i>♪ My voice it made
an avalanche ♪</i>

37
00:02:02.489 --> 00:02:05.550
<i>♪ And buried a
man I never knew ♪</i>

38
00:02:05.659 --> 00:02:08.857
<i>♪ And when he died
his widowed bride ♪</i>

39
00:02:08.929 --> 00:02:11.228
<i>♪ Met your daddy
and they made you ♪</i>

40
00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:13.927
<i>♪ I have only one
thing to do and that's ♪</i>

41
00:02:14.034 --> 00:02:15.764
<i>♪ Be the wave
that I am and then ♪</i>

42
00:02:15.869 --> 00:02:18.304
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

43
00:02:18.405 --> 00:02:20.567
<i>♪ I have only one
thing to do and that's ♪</i>

44
00:02:20.641 --> 00:02:22.109
<i>♪ Be the wave
that I am and then ♪</i>

45
00:02:22.209 --> 00:02:24.644
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

46
00:02:25.479 --> 00:02:27.277
<i>♪ I have only one
thing to do and that's ♪</i>

47
00:02:27.381 --> 00:02:29.247
<i>♪ Be the wave
that I am and then ♪</i>

48
00:02:29.316 --> 00:02:30.614
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

49
00:02:30.784 --> 00:02:32.309
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

50
00:02:32.419 --> 00:02:34.285
<i>♪ Sink back into the o... ♪</i>

51
00:02:34.354 --> 00:02:35.754
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

52
00:02:35.822 --> 00:02:37.415
<i>♪ Sink back into the o... ♪</i>

53
00:02:37.491 --> 00:02:39.084
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

54
00:02:39.292 --> 00:02:42.353
<i>♪ Sink back into the ocean ♪</i>

55
00:03:51.865 --> 00:03:53.891
You ready to go?

56
00:04:33.140 --> 00:04:34.802
Hey.

57
00:04:34.875 --> 00:04:37.811
Hi. Hey.

58
00:04:57.764 --> 00:04:59.699
How are you feeling?

59
00:05:02.435 --> 00:05:03.903
I'm fine.

60
00:05:15.882 --> 00:05:18.442
"Thou preparest
a table before me

61
00:05:18.552 --> 00:05:21.249
in the presence of mine enemies.

62
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:23.916
Thou anointest my head with oil.

63
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:25.982
My cup runneth over.

64
00:05:26.092 --> 00:05:29.551
Surely goodness and
mercy shall follow me

65
00:05:29.629 --> 00:05:31.723
all the days of my life.

66
00:05:31.798 --> 00:05:34.927
and I will dwell in the
house of the Lord forever."

67
00:05:35.001 --> 00:05:36.299
<i>♪ suspenseful music ♪</i>

68
00:05:36.403 --> 00:05:39.134
We will conclude our
service with a eulogy.

69
00:05:39.239 --> 00:05:42.437
I now invite Arthur's
son. Noah Solloway.

70
00:05:42.509 --> 00:05:46.002
to share some remembrances
of his beloved father.

71
00:05:57.324 --> 00:05:58.724
Um...

72
00:06:09.135 --> 00:06:11.070
Those of you who knew
my dad will... will know

73
00:06:11.137 --> 00:06:13.971
that we didn't always
get along so well.

74
00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:19.202
But I-I loved him.

75
00:06:21.982 --> 00:06:23.951
I did love him.

76
00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:27.714
Uh. wh-when I was a boy. uh...

77
00:06:27.787 --> 00:06:30.052
He used to take me
fishing in the... in the lake

78
00:06:30.123 --> 00:06:33.423
behind the house
where we grew up. and...

79
00:06:33.493 --> 00:06:35.121
<i>♪ solemn music ♪</i>

80
00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:43.265
Well. we both
really enjoyed that.

81
00:06:43.336 --> 00:06:45.635
My sister was...

82
00:06:47.674 --> 00:06:49.199
She and my dad were very close.

83
00:06:49.309 --> 00:06:53.804
I think she was...
She was more his type.

84
00:06:55.782 --> 00:06:57.614
But then she left.

85
00:07:08.895 --> 00:07:10.591
That was a hard time.

86
00:07:12.799 --> 00:07:15.098
That was a hard time.

87
00:07:15.201 --> 00:07:18.103
He had a... he had a hard
life. At least I think he did.

88
00:07:18.171 --> 00:07:21.164
To be... to be honest.
I-I never really knew him.

89
00:07:23.743 --> 00:07:25.473
Um...

90
00:07:28.815 --> 00:07:31.250
I always wanted to
ask more questions.

91
00:07:31.318 --> 00:07:36.313
You always think there's
gonna be... more time. but...

92
00:07:54.541 --> 00:07:56.271
Thank you for coming.

93
00:08:00.747 --> 00:08:03.444
Thank you. Mr. Solloway.
for those. um. words.

94
00:08:04.784 --> 00:08:08.277
We will now conclude our
service by singing. at his request.

95
00:08:08.388 --> 00:08:12.052
Arthur's favorite song. "Take
Me Out to the Ball Game."

96
00:08:14.627 --> 00:08:17.791
Thank you for telling that
story. Estelle. It was beautiful.

97
00:08:22.402 --> 00:08:23.893
I'm sorry.

98
00:08:23.970 --> 00:08:26.565
What is the matter with you?

99
00:08:26.639 --> 00:08:28.335
Nothing.

100
00:08:28.441 --> 00:08:30.273
Hey. there's your dad.

101
00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:31.777
Hey.

102
00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:33.473
Hey. Thanks for coming.

103
00:08:33.546 --> 00:08:35.538
I think Granddad
would have liked that.

104
00:08:35.648 --> 00:08:37.708
Short and sweet. No bullshit.

105
00:08:37.817 --> 00:08:41.310
Uh. Helen. thank you so much for
coming. You didn't have to do that.

106
00:08:41.388 --> 00:08:44.620
Well. I knew your father for 30
years. Where else would I be?

107
00:08:44.691 --> 00:08:46.819
Can I talk to you for a second?

108
00:08:49.763 --> 00:08:51.527
Come here. sweetie.

109
00:08:55.301 --> 00:08:56.894
You haven't returned
any of my calls.

110
00:08:56.970 --> 00:08:59.804
- I know.
- Why not?

111
00:08:59.906 --> 00:09:02.432
- I don't know.
- I... we need to talk.

112
00:09:02.542 --> 00:09:04.443
- About what?
- About what we're doing.

113
00:09:04.544 --> 00:09:07.070
About what our new
arrangement's going to be.

114
00:09:09.949 --> 00:09:11.850
- Are you still living at your sister's?
- Yes.

115
00:09:11.918 --> 00:09:13.614
Will you be getting
a place of your own?

116
00:09:13.720 --> 00:09:15.018
Eventually.

117
00:09:15.088 --> 00:09:17.421
Don't you want someplace
where you can be with the kids?

118
00:09:17.490 --> 00:09:19.789
- They can come to Nina's.
- I mean alone.

119
00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:21.604
I don't think they want
to be alone with me.

120
00:09:21.628 --> 00:09:23.790
Oh. that's ridiculous.
You're their father.

121
00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:25.991
- Stacey's afraid of me.
- She's not afraid of you.

122
00:09:26.099 --> 00:09:29.001
She's uncomfortable 'cause
she hasn't seen you in three years.

123
00:09:29.102 --> 00:09:30.900
That's why you need
to spend time with her.

124
00:09:32.572 --> 00:09:34.131
Okay. I'm trying. I swear I am.

125
00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:37.972
It's been... it's been two months.
Just give me a break. will ya?

126
00:09:38.078 --> 00:09:42.015
<i>♪ Tense music ♪</i>

127
00:09:45.752 --> 00:09:47.015
Um...

128
00:09:48.555 --> 00:09:51.218
What about us?

129
00:09:52.859 --> 00:09:54.350
What about us?

130
00:10:02.802 --> 00:10:05.101
Excuse me. Here.

131
00:10:05.205 --> 00:10:07.106
We got it.

132
00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:15.708
"Everyone the Father
gives to me will come to me.

133
00:10:15.782 --> 00:10:19.549
I will never turn away
anyone who believes in me.

134
00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:21.554
He who raised Jesus
Christ from the dead

135
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:23.920
will also give new life
to our mortal bodies

136
00:10:24.023 --> 00:10:25.719
through his indwelling spirit.

137
00:10:27.127 --> 00:10:31.724
My heart. therefore. is
glad. and my spirit rejoices.

138
00:10:31.798 --> 00:10:35.132
My body also shall rest in hope.

139
00:10:35.235 --> 00:10:37.636
You will show
me the path of life.

140
00:10:37.737 --> 00:10:40.104
In your presence
there is fullness of joy.

141
00:10:40.173 --> 00:10:43.940
and in your right hand
are pleasures forevermore."

142
00:10:45.445 --> 00:10:47.209
May the Lord bless and keep you.

143
00:10:47.313 --> 00:10:49.339
Noah!

144
00:10:49.449 --> 00:10:50.678
Noah!

145
00:10:56.589 --> 00:10:57.852
Noah!

146
00:11:06.933 --> 00:11:11.268
"The Lord lift up his countenance
upon him and give him peace." Amen.

147
00:11:11.371 --> 00:11:12.999
Amen.

148
00:11:13.072 --> 00:11:14.370
Amen.

149
00:11:17.377 --> 00:11:20.279
<i>♪ Solemn music ♪</i>

150
00:11:41.167 --> 00:11:43.534
Thank you so much for coming.

151
00:11:50.176 --> 00:11:51.906
- Thanks.
- Yes. of course.

152
00:11:52.011 --> 00:11:53.912
Thank you.

153
00:11:54.013 --> 00:11:55.379
- You okay?
- Mm-hmm.

154
00:11:55.481 --> 00:11:57.211
That was a lovely service. Nina.

155
00:11:57.317 --> 00:11:59.548
- Your father would be pleased.
- Thanks.

156
00:11:59.652 --> 00:12:02.019
You're coming back to the
house. though. aren't you?

157
00:12:02.088 --> 00:12:04.887
- Oh. uh. I don't know.
- Oh. come on.

158
00:12:04.958 --> 00:12:06.918
The kids. they haven't
seen each other in forever.

159
00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:08.428
Mine are so
looking forward to it.

160
00:12:08.528 --> 00:12:10.520
Do you think we should
come back to the house?

161
00:12:10.597 --> 00:12:12.463
Only if you want to.

162
00:12:17.937 --> 00:12:19.803
It's a school night. so...

163
00:12:19.906 --> 00:12:21.135
Right.

164
00:12:22.775 --> 00:12:25.540
This one time. Their
grandfather just died.

165
00:12:25.612 --> 00:12:27.240
The kids should be together.

166
00:12:27.313 --> 00:12:29.282
Nina. she gave her answer.

167
00:12:31.184 --> 00:12:33.517
- We should go.
- Okay.

168
00:12:33.620 --> 00:12:35.664
Martin needs more time with
his homework this semester

169
00:12:35.688 --> 00:12:37.816
because he's been coming
home with Cs and Ds.

170
00:12:37.890 --> 00:12:41.019
and if he fails out of another
school. he won't get into college.

171
00:12:41.127 --> 00:12:43.323
Thank you for coming. Helen.

172
00:12:43.396 --> 00:12:44.989
It was good to see you.

173
00:12:48.568 --> 00:12:51.697
His adviser wants to have a
parent-teacher conference next week.

174
00:12:51.804 --> 00:12:54.069
I think you should
be there. too.

175
00:12:54.173 --> 00:12:55.607
Uh. when is it?

176
00:12:57.677 --> 00:12:59.111
It's Thursday at four.

177
00:13:01.014 --> 00:13:02.778
Okay. I'll try.

178
00:13:09.055 --> 00:13:10.523
Let's go. Mom.

179
00:13:10.590 --> 00:13:13.116
Martin. come and say
goodbye to your father.

180
00:13:15.194 --> 00:13:16.423
Martin. did you hear me?

181
00:13:16.496 --> 00:13:18.176
I said. "Come and
say good-bye to your..."

182
00:13:18.231 --> 00:13:20.132
Don't make him. Helen. Please.

183
00:13:20.233 --> 00:13:23.135
<i>♪ Solemn music ♪</i>

184
00:13:49.996 --> 00:13:51.988
You have a lovely home.

185
00:13:52.065 --> 00:13:55.194
Oh. thank you. It's not mine.

186
00:13:55.301 --> 00:13:57.463
You're not the husband?

187
00:13:58.705 --> 00:14:00.139
I'm sorry. whose husband?

188
00:14:00.973 --> 00:14:03.306
I thought you were
Nina's husband.

189
00:14:03.376 --> 00:14:06.107
- Oh. no. no. no. I'm the brother.
- The brother.

190
00:14:07.413 --> 00:14:10.008
The brother who went to prison?

191
00:14:12.251 --> 00:14:16.450
You killed him. you
know. with your antics.

192
00:14:16.556 --> 00:14:19.253
He died of a broken heart.

193
00:14:19.425 --> 00:14:21.360
I thought he died of emphysema.

194
00:14:21.427 --> 00:14:23.862
You're a horror.

195
00:14:23.930 --> 00:14:25.558
Uh. excuse me. Donna.

196
00:14:25.631 --> 00:14:28.123
I hope you don't mind terribly.
I'm gonna steal my brother.

197
00:14:28.234 --> 00:14:30.760
- Where you going?
- To grieve.

198
00:14:32.739 --> 00:14:34.708
Come on.

199
00:14:38.945 --> 00:14:40.971
Here.

200
00:14:52.091 --> 00:14:54.083
Muscle relaxants.

201
00:15:05.938 --> 00:15:07.736
How was teaching this week?

202
00:15:07.840 --> 00:15:11.038
- It was fine.
- You have any fun?

203
00:15:11.110 --> 00:15:12.544
Not really.

204
00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:17.274
That's not the point. is it?
The point is to have a job.

205
00:15:17.383 --> 00:15:22.549
Well. if they like you.
then... maybe they'll give you

206
00:15:22.622 --> 00:15:25.285
a full-time gig at the
end of the semester.

207
00:15:25.391 --> 00:15:26.620
Maybe.

208
00:15:29.128 --> 00:15:32.292
You should really shave
that beard. You look insane.

209
00:15:35.501 --> 00:15:39.996
Noah. it's a good university.
and you're a convict.

210
00:15:40.072 --> 00:15:41.335
Ex-convict.

211
00:15:43.476 --> 00:15:45.911
Don't you think that's
part of the appeal?

212
00:15:52.151 --> 00:15:55.019
I'm sorry. I'm just...

213
00:15:55.087 --> 00:15:57.181
I'm having a hard time.

214
00:15:57.256 --> 00:16:01.023
Of course you're
having a hard time.

215
00:16:01.093 --> 00:16:04.552
But it's... it's
going to get better.

216
00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:07.395
- You just have to stay...
- Alive?

217
00:16:07.467 --> 00:16:09.595
I was going to say "positive."

218
00:16:19.111 --> 00:16:21.478
I think JP's tired of
having me around.

219
00:16:21.581 --> 00:16:23.812
Forget JP. I'll take care of it.

220
00:16:23.916 --> 00:16:25.976
He's just tired in general.

221
00:16:26.085 --> 00:16:28.281
It's just been a long summer.

222
00:16:36.395 --> 00:16:40.025
You know. you're the only
one who's ever forgiven me. Nin.

223
00:16:43.135 --> 00:16:47.800
Well. you forgave <i>me</i> once
for something pretty awful. so...

224
00:16:53.446 --> 00:16:55.677
Besides. I think
you're innocent.

225
00:17:01.387 --> 00:17:03.219
I'm not.

226
00:17:06.025 --> 00:17:07.687
<i>♪ Dark music ♪</i>

227
00:17:30.783 --> 00:17:33.275
<i>♪ solemn music ♪</i>

228
00:17:36.789 --> 00:17:38.485
Ow.

229
00:18:15.628 --> 00:18:18.063
- How could he never mention it?
- What?

230
00:18:18.130 --> 00:18:21.123
- You should have asked him.
- What is the matter with you?

231
00:18:21.233 --> 00:18:23.828
I would have never asked
him that. Just calm down.

232
00:18:23.936 --> 00:18:25.802
We're gonna figure it out. okay?

233
00:18:25.905 --> 00:18:28.306
What do you think
we're gonna do. Nina?

234
00:18:28.374 --> 00:18:31.105
How do you think we're
gonna pay for this trip?

235
00:18:31.177 --> 00:18:33.703
And for Christmas? It's
got to be some kind of joke.

236
00:18:33.813 --> 00:18:36.180
Your brother? Your
fucking brother?

237
00:18:39.285 --> 00:18:40.719
Everything okay?

238
00:18:43.656 --> 00:18:46.387
Your father's will
arrived this morning.

239
00:18:53.199 --> 00:18:54.428
Okay.

240
00:18:56.836 --> 00:18:58.828
He didn't have much to leave.

241
00:19:00.706 --> 00:19:02.937
He had his house...

242
00:19:03.042 --> 00:19:05.068
which he left to you.

243
00:19:05.177 --> 00:19:09.239
To me? Why?

244
00:19:09.348 --> 00:19:11.283
I don't know. Noah.

245
00:19:11.384 --> 00:19:13.353
Why don't you tell us?

246
00:19:14.820 --> 00:19:16.254
I don't know. either.

247
00:19:18.157 --> 00:19:19.750
You know he hated you.

248
00:19:19.825 --> 00:19:22.124
- JP.
- No. no. no.

249
00:19:22.194 --> 00:19:24.686
He could barely talk about you.

250
00:19:26.032 --> 00:19:29.298
She's the one who went
to see him every Sunday.

251
00:19:29.402 --> 00:19:32.600
She took him to church.
She took him to the doctor's.

252
00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:34.265
She changed his oxygen.

253
00:19:34.340 --> 00:19:37.469
She changed his fuckin' diapers.

254
00:19:37.576 --> 00:19:40.808
You know that we had to pay
for a live-in nurse at the end?

255
00:19:40.880 --> 00:19:44.214
Hmm? We're in something
of a hole here at the moment.

256
00:19:44.316 --> 00:19:47.548
- Doesn't matter.
- Oh. it doesn't? And why's that?

257
00:19:47.653 --> 00:19:49.781
Because you planted a
money tree in the backyard.

258
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:51.633
and we can just go out
and pick some fucking bills?

259
00:19:51.657 --> 00:19:53.819
- You're embarrassing me.
- I am. huh?

260
00:19:53.893 --> 00:19:56.158
Has he even paid
for groceries once?

261
00:19:56.228 --> 00:20:00.029
- Once since he's been here?
- Just go take a walk. please.

262
00:20:00.132 --> 00:20:03.330
- He's just like your fuckin' father.
- Get out!

263
00:20:03.402 --> 00:20:06.031
<i>♪ Tense music ♪</i>

264
00:20:08.908 --> 00:20:11.104
We needed that house. Nina.

265
00:20:16.882 --> 00:20:19.477
We needed it.

266
00:20:19.585 --> 00:20:22.612
Fuck it.

267
00:20:26.992 --> 00:20:28.460
Here. let me.

268
00:20:28.527 --> 00:20:29.995
No. I got it.

269
00:20:30.096 --> 00:20:31.826
I got it.

270
00:20:45.444 --> 00:20:46.969
I'll pick you up at six.

271
00:20:47.046 --> 00:20:50.744
No. I told you. I'll...
I'll find my own place.

272
00:20:50.850 --> 00:20:54.651
- You have no money.
- I have a little. I'll manage.

273
00:20:54.720 --> 00:20:58.680
Just... let me talk to JP.
okay? He will calm down.

274
00:20:58.758 --> 00:21:00.488
I don't want the house.

275
00:21:03.496 --> 00:21:06.830
Just tell JP he can have it.
He can sell it. I don't care.

276
00:21:06.899 --> 00:21:09.391
He can't have it.
Dad left it to you.

277
00:21:09.502 --> 00:21:12.097
I'm never going
back there. Nina.

278
00:21:12.204 --> 00:21:13.797
You know that.

279
00:21:15.708 --> 00:21:17.939
He was trying to apologize.

280
00:21:18.010 --> 00:21:20.445
Yeah. well. it's
too late for that.

281
00:21:20.513 --> 00:21:21.981
Fuckhead.

282
00:21:22.081 --> 00:21:24.915
It's way too late for that.

283
00:21:35.161 --> 00:21:37.187
"And so in the end.

284
00:21:37.296 --> 00:21:39.959
as she watched him
get back into his car

285
00:21:40.032 --> 00:21:42.228
and drive back
down the mountain.

286
00:21:42.334 --> 00:21:44.360
she couldn't help but wonder.

287
00:21:44.470 --> 00:21:47.406
would she feel
differently in the morning?

288
00:21:47.506 --> 00:21:50.408
Would she wake up again
with the sense of possibility

289
00:21:50.509 --> 00:21:52.978
she'd taken for
granted as a girl?

290
00:21:53.045 --> 00:21:55.173
In other words.

291
00:21:55.247 --> 00:21:57.409
is this moment the
end of her beginning

292
00:21:57.516 --> 00:21:59.348
or the beginning of her end?

293
00:22:00.386 --> 00:22:02.252
She was still
pondering the question

294
00:22:02.354 --> 00:22:06.849
when she heard the teakettle
whistle and turned from the window.

295
00:22:06.926 --> 00:22:09.521
When she looked back
again. his car was gone."

296
00:22:09.595 --> 00:22:11.723
<i>♪ suspenseful music ♪</i>

297
00:22:11.797 --> 00:22:13.231
The end.

298
00:22:21.106 --> 00:22:22.233
Mr. Solloway?

299
00:22:23.809 --> 00:22:26.574
Uh. yeah. th-thanks.
Thanks. Audrey.

300
00:22:30.983 --> 00:22:33.009
Questions. comments. concerns?

301
00:22:40.826 --> 00:22:42.317
Charlette?

302
00:22:43.495 --> 00:22:45.930
I thought it was
really elegant. Audrey.

303
00:22:45.998 --> 00:22:48.934
I liked the wind imagery.

304
00:22:49.001 --> 00:22:52.961
I felt your narrator's excitement when
the weather changed unexpectedly.

305
00:22:58.677 --> 00:23:00.703
You don't agree. Mr. Solloway?

306
00:23:03.048 --> 00:23:07.816
Uh... no. Charlette. I don't.
I thought it was very dull.

307
00:23:07.887 --> 00:23:10.857
Unless it was supposed
to be a satire. Was it?

308
00:23:12.758 --> 00:23:15.057
- No.
- No. I didn't think it was.

309
00:23:15.127 --> 00:23:17.756
Unfortunately. all that Audrey
has revealed here today

310
00:23:17.830 --> 00:23:21.631
is how shockingly unoriginal
her inner life actually is.

311
00:23:21.734 --> 00:23:24.499
It would probably behoove
you to turn off your computer.

312
00:23:24.603 --> 00:23:29.132
get off your couch. go outside and
risk some live human interactions

313
00:23:29.241 --> 00:23:32.439
so you could observe the
idiosyncrasies of actual behavior.

314
00:23:32.511 --> 00:23:33.945
Better yet. leave campus.

315
00:23:34.013 --> 00:23:35.572
Go visit some
struggling neighborhood

316
00:23:35.648 --> 00:23:37.810
and see real people try
to deal with real problems

317
00:23:37.883 --> 00:23:39.818
and then go home
and write about that.

318
00:23:39.885 --> 00:23:42.684
Or don't. I don't care. Just...

319
00:23:42.788 --> 00:23:45.656
Just don't bring your
diary in here again.

320
00:23:50.329 --> 00:23:51.627
Who's next?

321
00:23:54.700 --> 00:23:55.793
Why are you crying?

322
00:24:07.513 --> 00:24:09.072
Why was she crying?

323
00:24:09.181 --> 00:24:11.810
You eviscerated her. dude.

324
00:24:14.119 --> 00:24:16.748
Listen. kids. if... If
you want to be a writer.

325
00:24:16.822 --> 00:24:19.053
you better get used to
people hating your work.

326
00:24:19.124 --> 00:24:21.787
Why you got to denigrate
her experience. Mr. Solloway?

327
00:24:21.894 --> 00:24:24.159
It's not like your novels
have been paradigms

328
00:24:24.263 --> 00:24:26.926
of diverse socioeconomic
representation.

329
00:24:30.436 --> 00:24:34.601
<i>♪ Solemn music ♪</i>

330
00:25:14.813 --> 00:25:16.475
<i>Hi. yeah.</i>

331
00:25:16.582 --> 00:25:18.483
<i>this is. uh. Professor Solloway.</i>

332
00:25:18.584 --> 00:25:21.418
We spoke about the
apartment you're subletting.

333
00:25:21.487 --> 00:25:23.786
I'm... I'm... I'm
right outside now.

334
00:25:24.857 --> 00:25:27.793
Hey. Noah.

335
00:26:24.216 --> 00:26:25.514
You look great.

336
00:26:32.324 --> 00:26:33.815
Helen. it's okay.

337
00:26:33.892 --> 00:26:36.828
- Helen. tell me about the kids.
- They're fine.

338
00:26:36.895 --> 00:26:38.864
- Are they coming to visit?
- Yeah. of course.

339
00:26:38.964 --> 00:26:42.025
I just wanted to come myself
first to make sure it was safe. and...

340
00:26:45.037 --> 00:26:47.700
Oh. my God. I can't... I
can't believe you're in here.

341
00:26:47.773 --> 00:26:51.175
- It's okay.
- No. it's not okay.

342
00:26:51.243 --> 00:26:53.838
I can't believe you did
this. Why did you do this?

343
00:26:54.713 --> 00:26:56.375
Somebody needed
to take responsibility.

344
00:26:56.482 --> 00:26:57.677
No. that's not true.

345
00:26:57.749 --> 00:27:00.742
That's not how the justice
system works. Juries hang.

346
00:27:00.853 --> 00:27:02.082
Murderers go free.

347
00:27:02.187 --> 00:27:05.055
OJ Simpson wasn't convicted.
Why the fuck were you?

348
00:27:05.124 --> 00:27:07.889
Well. I didn't want to
leave anything to chance.

349
00:27:11.096 --> 00:27:14.123
Listen. it... there's nothing
we can do about it now.

350
00:27:14.233 --> 00:27:16.233
You and the kids are
safe. That's all that matters.

351
00:27:16.301 --> 00:27:18.146
- I'm gonna get you out of here.
- No. you're not.

352
00:27:18.170 --> 00:27:19.934
Yes. I am. I'm going
to speak to my father.

353
00:27:20.005 --> 00:27:22.565
- Your father.
- Yes. he knows the governor.

354
00:27:22.641 --> 00:27:23.939
He helped get him elected.

355
00:27:24.009 --> 00:27:26.171
Maybe he can get your
sentence transmuted.

356
00:27:26.278 --> 00:27:28.679
- You mean "commuted"?
- This is ridiculous.

357
00:27:28.780 --> 00:27:30.681
You can't be here.

358
00:27:31.517 --> 00:27:33.850
Not that bad. actually.

359
00:27:33.952 --> 00:27:36.387
I have my own cell. I
get plenty of exercise.

360
00:27:36.488 --> 00:27:38.787
I even like some of the
guys. They're very smart.

361
00:27:38.857 --> 00:27:41.793
They've... led
fascinating lives.

362
00:27:41.860 --> 00:27:44.038
Might even use a few of them
for research for my new novel.

363
00:27:44.062 --> 00:27:46.327
This isn't a writers' retreat.
Noah. You're incarcerated.

364
00:27:46.398 --> 00:27:47.866
Can't it be both?

365
00:27:50.969 --> 00:27:53.461
Helen. don't worry about me.

366
00:27:53.539 --> 00:27:56.031
I'm tougher than you think I am.

367
00:27:57.643 --> 00:28:00.238
And I owe this to you...

368
00:28:00.345 --> 00:28:02.143
after what I put you through.

369
00:28:02.247 --> 00:28:06.275
<i>♪ Solemn music ♪</i>

370
00:28:06.385 --> 00:28:09.048
Maybe this is my way
of wiping the slate clean.

371
00:28:12.291 --> 00:28:15.125
Besides. they're not gonna keep
me here for the full three years.

372
00:28:15.227 --> 00:28:16.889
I'll be out before you know it.

373
00:28:22.100 --> 00:28:24.160
And what about me?

374
00:28:26.705 --> 00:28:29.504
What am I supposed to
do while you're in here?

375
00:28:30.876 --> 00:28:33.311
Just wait.

376
00:28:39.151 --> 00:28:43.486
Consider the Arthurian
character <i>Merlin.</i> Merlin.

377
00:28:43.555 --> 00:28:49.187
born to a virgin who had
been impregnated by a devil.

378
00:28:49.261 --> 00:28:53.096
Merlin's internal integration
of the two sides to his soul

379
00:28:53.198 --> 00:28:57.192
establishes him as one of
our earliest archetypes for the...

380
00:28:57.269 --> 00:29:01.570
<i>Quel est le mot?</i> For... hello.

381
00:29:01.640 --> 00:29:04.940
You just popped up out of
nowhere. What's your name?

382
00:29:05.043 --> 00:29:06.534
Are you in the right place?

383
00:29:07.913 --> 00:29:11.042
Uh... no. no. sorry.

384
00:29:11.116 --> 00:29:12.584
I think I'm...

385
00:29:12.651 --> 00:29:14.483
Oh. I'm sorry to
put you on the spot.

386
00:29:14.586 --> 00:29:16.418
It's just that I've
asked everyone else

387
00:29:16.488 --> 00:29:19.390
to introduce themselves.
and I didn't see you there.

388
00:29:20.459 --> 00:29:23.918
Uh. I-I'm Noah... Solloway.

389
00:29:30.068 --> 00:29:32.799
<i>Ah. bienvenue.
Monsieur Solloway.</i>

390
00:29:32.904 --> 00:29:34.964
<i>Je suis Professeur Le Gall.</i>

391
00:29:39.344 --> 00:29:43.679
So... where were we?

392
00:29:43.782 --> 00:29:46.377
<i>Ah. oui.</i> The struggle.

393
00:29:46.952 --> 00:29:51.515
<i>Merlin.</i> Merlin is an archetype
for the struggle. perhaps. the...

394
00:29:51.623 --> 00:29:54.787
The war. <i>la guerre. oui...</i>
He's an archetype for the war

395
00:29:54.860 --> 00:29:56.829
between one's conscious mind

396
00:29:56.895 --> 00:29:59.956
and its self-destructive
subconscious desire.

397
00:30:01.266 --> 00:30:04.361
In Robert de Boron's
early version of the tale.

398
00:30:04.436 --> 00:30:07.736
Merlin's virtuous side
overcomes his demonic side.

399
00:30:07.806 --> 00:30:09.570
his holy destiny intact.

400
00:30:09.641 --> 00:30:13.203
Yet a slightly later version
of the exact same tale

401
00:30:13.278 --> 00:30:16.578
depicts Merlin as
irredeemably tainted

402
00:30:16.648 --> 00:30:18.378
by his infernal paternity.

403
00:30:18.450 --> 00:30:22.353
his lightness this time completely
destroyed by his darkness.

404
00:30:22.454 --> 00:30:26.357
In this post-Vulgate version.
we see the fictional shadow self

405
00:30:26.458 --> 00:30:30.520
become a manifestation
of the writer's own depravity.

406
00:30:30.629 --> 00:30:33.793
a shadow of a shadow.

407
00:30:33.865 --> 00:30:38.360
destined to be
destroyed by its creator.

408
00:30:38.470 --> 00:30:42.168
<i>♪ Solemn music ♪</i>

409
00:30:51.917 --> 00:30:54.853
<i>Monsieur Solloway.
Attendez. s'il vous plaît.</i>

410
00:30:57.756 --> 00:31:00.191
I'm just so pleased
to finally meet you.

411
00:31:00.258 --> 00:31:02.887
I feel that you and
I are kindred spirits.

412
00:31:02.961 --> 00:31:06.227
- Kindred spirits? How so?
- Silence is violence!

413
00:31:06.298 --> 00:31:08.893
No means no!

414
00:31:08.967 --> 00:31:10.936
Silence is violence!

415
00:31:11.002 --> 00:31:13.562
- Silence is violence!
- Was there a rape?

416
00:31:13.638 --> 00:31:17.040
I'm not sure. It's
apparently a bit murky.

417
00:31:17.109 --> 00:31:19.772
But I admire them.
these students.

418
00:31:19.878 --> 00:31:23.576
They're adamant when they
feel they're being mistreated.

419
00:31:23.648 --> 00:31:27.483
I was quite surprised.
It's not the same in France.

420
00:31:27.586 --> 00:31:29.646
They're after you.
too. you know.

421
00:31:29.755 --> 00:31:31.747
- Who?
- The students.

422
00:31:31.823 --> 00:31:34.258
Some of the faculty.

423
00:31:34.326 --> 00:31:36.591
There was a big
conversation before you arrived

424
00:31:36.661 --> 00:31:39.790
about whether it was safe
to have you on the campus.

425
00:31:39.865 --> 00:31:41.299
Why?

426
00:31:41.366 --> 00:31:43.631
You just got out of prison. no?

427
00:31:43.702 --> 00:31:45.637
Oh. okay.

428
00:31:45.704 --> 00:31:47.866
And you're a murderer. yes?

429
00:31:47.973 --> 00:31:49.703
Silence is violence!

430
00:31:49.808 --> 00:31:51.538
No means no!

431
00:31:51.643 --> 00:31:53.373
No means no!

432
00:31:53.478 --> 00:31:55.413
Silence is violence!

433
00:31:55.514 --> 00:32:00.282
So. are you happy here?
Are you glad you came?

434
00:32:02.387 --> 00:32:04.947
Well. it's. uh... it's
better than prison.

435
00:32:08.226 --> 00:32:11.856
I'll have to remember that on the
days I'm feeling particularly depressed.

436
00:32:13.365 --> 00:32:15.061
Why are you depressed?

437
00:32:15.133 --> 00:32:19.571
Well. "depressed" is probably
wrong. I just feel... bored. <i>Ennui.</i>

438
00:32:19.638 --> 00:32:21.129
I thought I'd come to America

439
00:32:21.239 --> 00:32:23.140
and have a grand
adventure. you know?

440
00:32:23.241 --> 00:32:26.006
- Mm.
- I'd be at a famous university.

441
00:32:26.111 --> 00:32:29.104
arguing with passionate
students late into the nights.

442
00:32:29.181 --> 00:32:31.946
And instead. it's. um...

443
00:32:32.017 --> 00:32:33.315
Instead. it's New Jersey.

444
00:32:33.418 --> 00:32:35.250
Yes.

445
00:32:35.320 --> 00:32:39.690
Where everyone
is just so... nice.

446
00:32:42.160 --> 00:32:45.892
Before I began. I got
a kind of a... a <i>merde...</i>

447
00:32:45.997 --> 00:32:48.626
How do you say? A
sermon from the dean

448
00:32:48.700 --> 00:32:51.260
about making the
students feel secure.

449
00:32:51.369 --> 00:32:54.168
I thought. "Secure.
at a university? Why?"

450
00:32:54.239 --> 00:32:58.040
I don't remember feeling secure
when I was in school. do you?

451
00:32:58.109 --> 00:32:59.202
- No.
- You see?

452
00:32:59.277 --> 00:33:02.270
I said. <i>"Monsieur.</i> surely
our job is to challenge them.

453
00:33:02.380 --> 00:33:04.906
to unsettle. to make
them feel insecure. no?"

454
00:33:05.016 --> 00:33:06.245
- Mm-hmm.
- No.

455
00:33:09.054 --> 00:33:10.955
Yeah. it wasn't
always like this.

456
00:33:11.056 --> 00:33:14.220
I remember back when I
was teaching high school.

457
00:33:14.292 --> 00:33:17.160
I started noticing
the change after 9/11.

458
00:33:17.262 --> 00:33:19.493
- Mm.
- The president came on the television

459
00:33:19.598 --> 00:33:21.624
and started talking about
keeping Americans safe.

460
00:33:21.733 --> 00:33:24.567
and suddenly all the
students were repeating it.

461
00:33:24.636 --> 00:33:28.505
And these current students.
they're... they're even younger.

462
00:33:28.607 --> 00:33:32.601
and they've grown up
on a whole rhetoric of s...

463
00:33:32.677 --> 00:33:36.307
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

464
00:33:36.381 --> 00:33:38.612
Noah. are you all right?

465
00:33:39.384 --> 00:33:42.821
Uh. yeah. Yeah. uh...

466
00:33:48.894 --> 00:33:51.261
I'm having a small
dinner party tonight.

467
00:33:51.363 --> 00:33:52.854
Would you like to come?

468
00:33:55.534 --> 00:33:56.900
Sure. Okay.

469
00:33:57.602 --> 00:33:59.127
<i>Très bien.</i>

470
00:34:03.041 --> 00:34:04.942
So sorry I'm late.

471
00:34:06.778 --> 00:34:08.212
Shall we?

472
00:34:11.816 --> 00:34:13.910
You're teaching only
one class. correct?

473
00:34:13.985 --> 00:34:17.820
That's right. yeah. I'm
hoping for more next semester.

474
00:34:17.923 --> 00:34:19.323
How's it going?

475
00:34:19.424 --> 00:34:20.949
Well. I think.

476
00:34:21.026 --> 00:34:22.494
I think it's going well.

477
00:34:23.929 --> 00:34:25.659
No trouble?

478
00:34:26.765 --> 00:34:27.994
Nope.

479
00:34:30.001 --> 00:34:31.697
The job ends in December?

480
00:34:32.704 --> 00:34:37.938
Yes. but. uh. there's a possibility
I'll be invited back for the spring term.

481
00:34:38.009 --> 00:34:39.637
And if you're not?

482
00:34:42.847 --> 00:34:44.281
Uh...

483
00:34:45.350 --> 00:34:46.750
I don't know.

484
00:34:46.851 --> 00:34:48.945
It's important that you stay
employed. Mr. Solloway.

485
00:34:49.054 --> 00:34:51.023
as part of your rehabilitation.

486
00:34:51.089 --> 00:34:52.421
I know.

487
00:34:53.592 --> 00:34:55.458
Are you waiting for somebody?

488
00:34:55.560 --> 00:34:56.960
No. no. sorry. I ju...

489
00:34:57.062 --> 00:35:00.590
How's your living situation?
You still at your sister's?

490
00:35:00.699 --> 00:35:01.962
Uh. no.

491
00:35:02.067 --> 00:35:05.401
- No? You moved?
- As of today... uh. tonight.

